THE Zanzibar Cooperatives Society (ZASCOS) and the Moshi Co-operative University (MoCU) have signed Memorandum of Understanding (MoU), paving way for strengthening relations that will see cooperatives in the Isles improve efficiency. Zanzibar Minister of State- Office of the President (Labour, Economy, and Investments) Mr Mudrik Ramadhan Soraga witnessed the signing of documents, saying that the Zanzibar government was ready to work with the MoCU to improve the performance of cooperatives here. “We want productive cooperatives for development. The agreement will help strengthen the cooperatives in Zanzibar including provision of trainings, and conduct various research related to cooperatives to accelerate the growth of the associations,” Mr Soraga said. The Registrar of Cooperatives and Director of the Co-operatives Development Department, Mr Khamis Daudi Simba, said that following the agreement, they are optimistic to achieve success and bring about productivity and changes in the running of cooperatives. He said various studies will be conducted on issues related to strengthening cooperatives, saying further that MoCU in collaboration with Zanzibar cooperatives will also identify challenges that hinder cooperatives from making progress. Prof Gervas Machimu from MoCU said that in order for the societies to progress, it is important that co-operatives training be provided to build awareness in the community about the activities of co-operatives that can liberate the citizens economically.